text: every time I open up Facebook I see
another person getting married or having
a kid and I'm over here searching for
plane tickets 95 percent of my expenses
are travel related hotels experiences
food is it bad is it wrong that I'm not
like my friends society puts a lot of
pressure on us to go to a good school
get a high paying job get married and
have kids that is the normal way to live
a life and there's absolutely nothing
wrong with it I fully appreciate and
respect that there's no issue with
having kids at a young age but me on the
other hand I am far removed from the
norm I haven't even thought about a
mortgage or buying a car having kids is
certainly in my future plans but not yet
as a 26 year old I'm making a full-time
income through travel videos which is a
lifestyle I carved for myself through
very hard work I am touching a computer
a phone or a camera 15 hours a day and I
spent almost all of my money on travel
and experiences today I will be
experiencing the true hidden culture of
Ethiopia in a very special place I enjoy
taking risks I can't see going to
unknown places stepping out of my
comfort zone I guess I'm just different
or is it my generation that's different
somehow it feels like I'm doing life
wrong when there is so much pressure to
live the easy way I'm making this video
to share my realizations and see if
anyone out there can connect with my
feelings if you can please share your
thoughts below I'm drew pinsky and if
you like my travel videos please click
Subscribe and join me as I plan to visit
every country in the world
